That will identify exactly where the flow stops.

## 7. Your current logs only prove the endpoint succeeded

This line:

```text
POST /partner-repository/internal/users/snapshots ... 200 OK
```

only proves that the HTTP request completed. It does not prove that:

* a new user was inserted;
* the create branch was used;
* Ping was called;
* Ping returned successfully.

Also, this startup line:

```text
Liquibase did not run because 'shouldRun' property was set to false
```

is separate. It means your new Ping columns may not have been created by Liquibase in this environment. Check the database schema before relying on fields such as:

```text
ping_resource_id
ping_sync_status
ping_last_synced_at
ping_last_error
```

The first correction is to locate the service method behind `/internal/users/snapshots` and place the Ping call directly in its new-user branch.
